   <text type="translation">
      <body>
         <pb facs="1871_01_02_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_R_Gaertner_Augustenfelde_1.tif" n="1"/>
         <p>Augustenfelde, 2nd January 1871.<lb/>
            <lb/>
            <lb/>Messrs. L. Kniffler &amp; Co. Yokohama.<lb/>I am taking the opportunity today
                to ask you kindly to pay out to<lb/>Mr. Carl Kramer in Yokohama, on production of
                the instructions sent to him <del rend="overstrike">b</del>
            <lb/>by me, the amount of Mex. Dollar 63,58 ⟨not⟩ on my account<lb/> and secondly to
                remit please the amount of $. 260- in <lb/>⟨14/1. £ 56.12/1 c 4/4¼⟩ London bill of
                exchange at variable term to<lb/> Messrs. Conrad &amp; Simon in Berlin,
                Stallschreiber Str. 30.<lb/>In line with the enclosed bill of lading I am sending
                you 500 Rios<lb/>⟨Memf1⟩ with the request to credit me for them and I am truly sorry
                <lb/>not yet to be able to pay my entire debt with you, which, however, <lb/>will be
                the case shortly, regardless of whether my brother Conrad<lb/>is travelling to
                Yokohama at the next possible occasion. <lb/>Most sincerely and respectfully <lb/>R.
                Gaertner<lb/>P. S. In line with the bill of lading further also:<lb/>Mex $ 40._
                Yokohama bank notes<lb/>for kind crediting, and against this to pay on my account
                <lb/>the amount of <lb/>⟨Memf 1⟩ Mex$ 63.99<lb/>against receipt to Mr. G. Farley,
                Yokohama,<lb/>and please to excuse the inconvenience caused.<lb/>Yours sincerely and
                respectfully <lb/>R. Gaertner<lb/>T. Gaertner</p>
         <pb facs="1871_01_02_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_R_Gaertner_Augustenfelde_2.tif" n="2"/>
         <pb facs="1871_01_02_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_R_Gaertner_Augustenfelde_3.tif" n="3"/>
